target: renderer
validations:
  - name: map_and_entities_draw
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the renderer draws the tile grid and all entity types.
        The canvas should show a visible grid of colored tiles (green grass,
        beige paths, blue water, orange entrance). Enclosures should appear
        as colored rectangles matching their biome. Animals should appear as
        small colored circles within enclosures. Visitors should appear as
        tiny dots moving along paths.
  - name: camera_panning
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the camera pans correctly. Pressing arrow keys or moving
        the mouse to the canvas edge should scroll the view. The map should
        shift smoothly in the opposite direction. The camera should stop at
        the map boundaries and not scroll into empty space. All entities
        should remain correctly positioned relative to their tiles as the
        camera moves.
  - name: ui_overlays_visible
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that UI overlays render on top of the game world. The HUD bar
        at the top should display current money, animal count, and visitor
        count. The sidebar should be visible on the right side of the screen.
        UI elements should remain fixed in screen space and not move when the
        camera pans.
